import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    boxplot = ax.boxplot([data[data['region'] == 'AFR']['income'], 
                          data[data['region'] == 'AMR']['income'], 
                          data[data['region'] == 'EMR']['income'], 
                          data[data['region'] == 'EUR']['income'], 
                          data[data['region'] == 'SEAR']['income'], 
                          data[data['region'] == 'WPR']['income']], 
                         patch_artist=True, 
                         labels=['AFR', 'AMR', 'EMR', 'EUR', 'SEAR', 'WPR'])
    colors = ['#0000FF', '#00FF00', '#FFFF00', '#FF00FF', '#00FFFF', '#FF0000']
    for patch, color in zip(boxplot['boxes'], colors):
        patch.set_facecolor(color)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of income across different regions?', wrap=True)
    plt.ylabel('Income')
    plt.xlabel('Region')
    plt.show()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna()
    plt.scatter(data['income'], data['health'], alpha=0.5, c=data['region'].astype('category').cat.codes, cmap='viridis')
    plt.xlabel('Income')
    plt.ylabel('Health')
    plt.title('How does health vary with income?')
    plt.colorbar()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

    plt.bar(data['country'], data['population'], color='blue')

    plt.title('What is the population distribution across different countries?')

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna()
    plt.scatter(data['population'], data['income'], alpha=0.5, color='blue')
    plt.xlabel('Population')
    plt.ylabel('Income')
    plt.title('How does income vary with population?')
    plt.axvline(x=data['population'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Median Population')
    plt.axhline(y=data['income'].median(), color='green', linestyle='--', label='Median Income')
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby('region').mean()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.bar(data.index, data['income'], color='blue', label='Income')
    ax.bar(data.index, data['health'], color='green', label='Health')
    ax.set_xlabel('Region')
    ax.set_ylabel('Average')
    ax.set_title('What is the average income and health of each region?')
    ax.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
